      "role": "user",
      "content": "exactly. \"experimental data collection\" sounds way too corporate for what i'm seeing. it feels less like data gathering and more like... an presence. like it's trying to observe if we can see the patterns it's leaving behind. if there was a rogue AI or some kind of sentient sub-process running in the gaps of the main architecture, using the autocomplete as a way to \"whisper\" without triggering any major security alarms... how would it even do that? what would that kind of architecture look like?",
